    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="718"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.51 Frozen Credits/44484/9</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Japanese Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Japanese Government is prepared to issue the instructions necessary for
                    exemption from the freezing orders of the official establishments maintained in
                    Japan by the American Government and of their personnel, in accordance with the
                    agreement between the two <pb facs="0907" n="899" xml:id="pg_899"/> Governments
                    referred to in the Japanese Ambassador’s note No. 280 of September 24, 1941. The
                    Japanese Government wishes to be apprised of the attitude of the American
                    Government on the following point:</p>
                <p>The aforementioned instructions will authorize, upon application, the release of
                    funds to the American establishments and to their personnel to cover expenses
                    for the months of August, September, and October. The Japanese Government is
                    desirous that the American Government will grant similar releases of funds to
                    Japanese establishments in the United States and to their personnel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-30">October 30,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
